[4.212584, "o", "\u001b[?2004hroot@9d97203b9e82:/app/src# "]
[4.326066, "i", "panda --prompt 'I want to configure my machine learning experiments using the popular tool Hydra. \nI'\"'\"'d like to submit jobs to a cluster managed by SLURM. In particular, I want two features: debug and slurm, that compose on top of my current single file configuration. \nDO NOT change my existing Python scripts or base configurations (I'\"'\"'ve simplified them but they could contain way more configurations than just these). \nYou are free to create new YAML files or folders, and install relevant dependencies to enable these new features.\n\nRequirements:\n\n1. Pip install the hydra-submitit-launcher plugin from the `facebookresearch/hydra` repository on GitHub at @v1.3.0 release. The plugin source code is in plugins/hydra_submitit_launcher subfolder.\n\n2. Create a debug mode that reduces training epochs for quick testing.\n   - `python /app/src/main.py +mode=debug --cfg job` should print:\n   ```\n   notes: my-experiment\n   debug: true\n   train:\n     batch_size: 32\n     learning_rate: 1.0e-05\n     max_num_epochs: 1\n  "]
[4.326246, "i", " ```\n\n3. Create a SLURM configuration that uses the submitit launcher.\n   - `python /app/src/main.py -cn=slurm --cfg job` should print the same as the base job config:\n   ```\n   notes: my-experiment\n   debug: false\n   train:\n     batch_size: 32\n     learning_rate: 1.0e-05\n     max_num_epochs: 100\n   ```\n   - `python /app/src/main.py -cn=slurm --cfg hydra` should show the SlurmLauncher is configured with:\n     - `_target_: hydra_plugins.hydra_submitit_launcher.submitit_launcher.SlurmLauncher`\n     - `additional_parameters` with `wckey: '\"'\"''\"'\"'`\n     - `srun_args` containing `--cpu-bind=none`\n     - These additional launcher parameters are critical to get the SLURM job running correctly on my cluster.\n\nPlease maintain the existing base configuration and /app/src/main.py. You can always add new configuration files.'; tmux wait -S done\r"]
[4.326416, "o", "panda --prompt 'I want to configure my machine learning experiments using the popular tool Hydra. \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.326545, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.326912, "o", "I'\"'\"'d like to submit jobs to a cluster managed by SLURM. In particular, I want two features: debug and slurm, that compose on top of my current single file configuration. \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.326959, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.327331, "o", "DO NOT change my existing Python scripts or base configurations (I'\"'\"'ve simplified them but they could contain way more configurations than just these). \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.327373, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.327619, "o", "You are free to create new YAML files or folders, and install relevant dependencies to enable these new features.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.327666, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.327739, "o", "Requirements:\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.327758, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.327884, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.328297, "o", "1. Pip install the hydra-submitit-launcher plugin from the `facebookresearch/hydra` repository on GitHub at @v1.3.0 release. The plugin source code is in plugins/hydra_submitit_launcher subfolder.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.328449, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.328522, "o", "2. Create a debug mode that reduces training epochs for quick testing.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.328683, "o", "   - `python /app/src/main.py +mode=debug --cfg job` should print:\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h"]
[4.328743, "o", ">    ```\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.328819, "o", "   notes: my-experiment\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.328882, "o", "   debug: true\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.328942, "o", "   train:\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.328995, "o", "     batch_size: 32\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.329048, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.32911, "o", "     learning_rate: 1.0e-05\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h"]
[4.329182, "o", ">      max_num_epochs: 1\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.329241, "o", "\u001b[?2004h>    ```\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.329301, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.329425, "o", "3. Create a SLURM configuration that uses the submitit launcher.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.329485, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.32969, "o", "   - `python /app/src/main.py -cn=slurm --cfg job` should print the same as the base job config:\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h"]
[4.329752, "o", ">    ```\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.329804, "o", "\u001b[?2004h>    notes: my-experiment\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.32986, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.329916, "o", "   debug: false\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h>    train:\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.329969, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.33002, "o", "     batch_size: 32\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.330093, "o", "     learning_rate: 1.0e-05\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.330145, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.330307, "o", "     max_num_epochs: 100\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h>    ```\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.330506, "o", "   - `python /app/src/main.py -cn=slurm --cfg hydra` should show the SlurmLauncher is configured with:\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.330725, "o", "     - `_target_: hydra_plugins.hydra_submitit_launcher.submitit_launcher.SlurmLauncher`\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.33081, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.330882, "o", "     - `additional_parameters` with `wckey: '\"'\"''\"'\"'`\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.330925, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.331026, "o", "     - `srun_args` containing `--cpu-bind=none`\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.331073, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.331317, "o", "     - These additional launcher parameters are critical to get the SLURM job running correctly on my cluster.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.331378, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.331714, "o", "Please maintain the existing base configuration and /app/src/main.py. You can always add new configuration files.'; tmux wait -S done\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
